headline.main: After Long Gestation, Scion FR-S Makes Auto Show Debut

docs.snippet: The 200-horsepower two-plus-two coupe was developed in tandem with the Subaru BRZ coupe....
docs.abstract: The 200-horsepower two-plus-two coupe was developed in tandem with the Subaru BRZ coupe.
docs.lead_paragraph: What is it? The name says it all, according to Toyota: FR-S stands for "front-engine, rear-wheel-drive, sport." The 2-plus-2 coupe measures nearly a foot longer than a Corolla and carries decidedly sportier pretensions. Its Toyota-branded equivalent, the FT, was displayed at the Tokyo auto show in December, but Toyota clearly wants Scion to get a dose of performance cred, which was previously available only from the tC. The FR-S was previewed as a concept at the 2011 New York auto show.

docs.lead_paragraph: OTTAWA -- The hedge fund manager William A. Ackman said Monday that he would wage a proxy battle to replace the directors and the chief executive of the Canadian Pacific Railway after it rejected his plan to bring in a former rival to run the company.
